---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PasswordGate from '../components/PasswordGate.astro';
---

<Layout title="Villa Curation - Studio Kaku" description="Studio Kaku curates art, objects, and interiors for private residences across Japan - rooted in Hokkaido craft and contemporary Japanese art." noindex={true}>

  <PasswordGate password="kaku-villa" />

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="min-h-[90vh] grid md:grid-cols-2 bg-brand-text">
    <div class="flex flex-col justify-between px-8 md:px-16 pt-32 pb-28 md:pt-48 md:pb-40">
      <p class="text-[10px] tracking-[0.25em] uppercase text-brand-accent"
        data-en="Art · Curation · Space · Hokkaido"
        data-ja="アート・キュレーション・空間・北海道"
      >Art · Curation · Space · Hokkaido</p>
      <div>
        <h1 class="font-display uppercase leading-[1.08] text-brand-bg" style="font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 4.5rem);" data-fade-text
          data-en={`A space that<br />speaks <em class="not-italic text-brand-accent">for itself</em>`}
          data-ja={`空間が、<br />自ら<em class="not-italic text-brand-accent">語る。</em>`}
        >
          A space that<br />speaks <em class="not-italic text-brand-accent">for itself</em>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-brand-bg/45 text-sm leading-relaxed max-w-sm mt-7" data-fade-text style="transition-delay:80ms"
          data-en="Studio Kaku curates art, objects, and interiors for private villas at Kamui resort. A considered space is one guests remember - and return to."
          data-ja="Studio Kakuは、カムイリゾートのプライベートヴィラのためにアート、オブジェ、インテリアをキュレーションします。丁寧に考えられた空間は、ゲストの記憶に残り、また訪れたくなる場所になります。"
        >
          Studio Kaku curates art, objects, and interiors for private villas at Kamui resort. A considered space is one guests remember - and return to.
        </p>
      </div>
      <p class="text-brand-bg/25 text-[11px] tracking-wide"
        data-en="Studio Kaku · Villa curation"
        data-ja="Studio Kaku · ヴィラキュレーション"
      >Studio Kaku · Villa curation</p>
    </div>
    <div class="hidden md:block border-l border-brand-bg/[0.08] overflow-hidden">
      <img src="/images/catalogue/room-tatami-chair.jpg" alt="" class="w-full h-full object-cover" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The collection / artists -->
  <section class="px-8 md:px-16 pt-16 pb-10 md:pt-24 md:pb-16 border-t border-brand-border">
    <p class="text-[10px] tracking-[0.25em] uppercase text-brand-accent mb-8 flex items-center gap-4">
      <span data-en="The collection" data-ja="コレクション">The collection</span>
      <span class="block h-px w-12 bg-brand-accent/40"></span>
    </p>
    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-end gap-6 md:gap-24 mb-16">
      <h2 class="font-display uppercase leading-[1.1] shrink-0" style="font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.25rem);"
        data-en="Japanese artists<br />we work with"
        data-ja="ともに歩む<br />日本のアーティスト"
      >
        Japanese artists<br />we work with
      </h2>
      <p class="text-brand-muted text-sm leading-relaxed max-w-sm pb-1"
        data-en="From established voices to emerging makers - art available as prints, editions, and originals."
        data-ja="確立されたアーティストから新進の作家まで——プリント、エディション、オリジナル作品として購入可能です。"
      >
        From established voices to emerging makers - art available as prints, editions, and originals.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-5 gap-4 md:gap-5">
      {[
        { img: '/images/artists/artist-1.jpg', bio: 'Paintings that flow like water - vivid colour and undulating lines, built up in layers and sanded back to reveal what lies beneath.', bioJa: '水が流れるような絵画——鮮やかな色彩と波打つ線が層を重ね、研き出されることで内側が現れる。' },
        { img: '/images/artists/artist-2.jpg', bio: 'Contemporary artist from the Ainu community in Akan, Hokkaido. Traditional craft reimagined through modern design and everyday objects.', bioJa: '北海道阿寒のアイヌコミュニティ出身のコンテンポラリーアーティスト。伝統工芸をモダンデザインと日用品を通じて再解釈する。' },
        { img: '/images/artists/artist-3.jpg', bio: 'Based in Shiraoi since 2002. Sculpture, painting, and installation exploring the boundaries between earth and sky.', bioJa: '2002年から白老を拠点に活動。彫刻、絵画、インスタレーションを通じて大地と空の境界を探求する。', contain: true },
        { img: '/images/artists/artist-4.jpg', bio: 'Hokkaido-born woodworker. Construction, joinery, and renovation inform a practice that began two years ago.', bioJa: '北海道生まれの木工家。建築・木工・リノベーションの経験を活かし、2年前から制作活動を開始。' },
        { img: '/images/artists/artist-5.jpg', bio: 'Studied at Chelsea College of Arts. Organic shapes and pastel tones - work that has exhibited in Japan, London, and beyond.', bioJa: 'チェルシー・カレッジ・オブ・アーツで学ぶ。有機的なフォルムとパステルトーンの作品は、日本・ロンドンをはじめ世界各地で展示されている。' },
        { img: '/images/artists/artist-6.jpg', bio: 'Fluid lines and vivid colour expressing everyday emotion. First solo exhibition this year.', bioJa: '流れるような線と鮮やかな色彩で日常の感情を表現する。今年、初の個展を開催。' },
        { img: '/images/artists/artist-7.jpg', bio: 'Born in Okinawa. Calligraphy reimagined through light and contemporary expression - rooted in Zen and Okinawan tradition.', bioJa: '沖縄出身。禅と沖縄の伝統を根底に、光とコンテンポラリーな表現を通じて書を再解釈する。' },
        { img: '/images/artists/artist-8.jpg', bio: 'The Couple series - sculpture, painting, and drawing exploring invisible human connection through intertwined form.', bioJa: '「カップルシリーズ」——絡み合うフォルムを通じて、見えない人間のつながりを彫刻・絵画・ドローイングで探求する。' },
        { img: '/images/artists/artist-9.jpg', bio: 'Ceramics that restore broken things. Clay cracked, fired, glazed, and reassembled - fragility made permanent.', bioJa: '壊れたものを再生する陶芸。割れた土を焼き、釉薬をかけ、組み直す——儚さを永遠に変える試み。', position: 'left center' },
        { img: '/images/artists/artist-10.jpg', bio: 'Born in Osaka. Now farming, fishing, and making art from a village on the Chiba coast.', bioJa: '大阪生まれ。千葉の海岸沿いの村で農業、漁業、そしてアート制作に取り組む。' },
      ].map((artist, i) => (
        <div data-fade style={`transition-delay:${(i % 5) * 60}ms`}>
          <div class="aspect-[3/4] overflow-hidden mb-3">
            <img src={artist.img} alt="" class={`w-full h-full ${artist.contain ? 'object-contain bg-brand-bg' : 'object-cover'}`} style={artist.position ? `object-position: ${artist.position}` : ''} />
          </div>
          <p class="text-brand-muted text-[11px] leading-relaxed" data-en={artist.bio} data-ja={artist.bioJa}>{artist.bio}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Local goods -->
  <section class="px-8 md:px-16 pt-16 pb-10 md:pt-24 md:pb-16 border-t border-brand-border bg-brand-border/20">
    <p class="text-[10px] tracking-[0.25em] uppercase text-brand-accent mb-8 flex items-center gap-4">
      <span data-en="Local goods" data-ja="地元の品々">Local goods</span>
      <span class="block h-px w-12 bg-brand-accent/40"></span>
    </p>
    <h2 class="font-display uppercase leading-[1.1] mb-8" style="font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.25rem);"
      data-en="Hokkaido,<br />made by hand"
      data-ja="北海道、<br />手で作られたもの。"
    >
      Hokkaido,<br />made by hand
    </h2>
    <p class="text-brand-muted text-sm leading-relaxed max-w-lg mb-14"
      data-en="These are the objects that sit quietly in a room and make guests ask where you found them. Each piece is made in Hokkaido - available as part of a package, or added individually."
      data-ja="部屋に静かに佇み、ゲストが「どこで手に入れたの？」と尋ねずにはいられないオブジェ。すべて北海道で作られた品々で、パッケージの一部として、または単品でお選びいただけます。"
    >
      These are the objects that sit quietly in a room and make guests ask where you found them. Each piece is made in Hokkaido - available as part of a package, or added individually.
    </p>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-px bg-brand-border">
      {[
        { title: 'Ainu Mino Ceramics', titleJa: 'アイヌ美濃焼', body: 'Two white square plates with a raised Ainu geometric pattern in warm taupe. Handmade in Biratori, a town with one of Hokkaido\'s oldest Ainu communities.', bodyJa: '温かみのあるタウプ色でアイヌの幾何学模様が浮き彫りにされた白い正方形の皿が2枚。北海道最古のアイヌコミュニティのひとつ、平取で手作りされています。', price: '¥20,000 · Biratori', img: '/images/products/ainu-ceramics.jpg' },
        { title: 'Cara Wooden Plates', titleJa: 'カラ 木製プレート', body: 'Three nested round plates turned from light Hokkaido timber. A set that works on the table or displayed on a shelf.', bodyJa: '北海道の淡い色の木材から削り出された丸いプレート3枚セット。テーブルでも棚に飾っても絵になります。', price: '¥11,000 · Asahikawa', img: '/images/products/cara-plate.jpg' },
        { title: 'Flower Cut Glass', titleJa: '花切子グラス', body: 'A teal cut glass tumbler with a floral pattern and amber layered base - made using the Otaru kiriko glass-cutting tradition.', bodyJa: '小樽切子の伝統技法で作られた、花柄とアンバーベースが美しいティールのカットグラスタンブラー。', price: '¥49,000 · Otaru', img: '/images/products/flower-glass.jpg' },
        { title: 'Sapporo Ceramic Plate', titleJa: '札幌陶器プレート', body: 'A wide, shallow plate with a sandy textured glaze. Shown here set at a table - the kind of piece that improves with use.', bodyJa: '砂のような釉薬が施された幅広の浅皿。テーブルに映える一枚——使うほどに味わいが増します。', price: '¥10,000 · Asahikawa', img: '/images/products/sapporo-plate.jpg' },
        { title: 'Blue Cut Glass', titleJa: 'ブルー切子グラス', body: 'Deep cobalt blue with a repeating circular cut pattern across the entire body. A bold piece from the Otaru glass tradition.', bodyJa: '全体に繰り返す円形のカットパターンが施された深いコバルトブルー。小樽ガラスの伝統から生まれた力強い一品。', price: '¥27,500 · Otaru', img: '/images/products/wine-glass.jpg' },
        { title: 'Foldable Rain Boots', titleJa: '折りたたみレインブーツ', body: 'Bright teal boots with a pink sole and yellow trim that pack flat into their own pouch. Practical for Hokkaido\'s unpredictable weather.', bodyJa: '専用ポーチに平たく収納できる、ピンクソールとイエロートリムのティールブーツ。北海道の変わりやすい天気にも対応。', price: '¥20,000 · Otaru', img: '/images/products/rain-boots.jpg' },
        { title: 'Higashikawa Ceramics', titleJa: '東川焼', body: 'A workshop range of mugs and vases in blue-green gradient glaze. Each piece is slightly different.', bodyJa: '青緑のグラデーション釉薬のマグカップと花瓶のワークショップシリーズ。一点一点が少しずつ異なります。', price: 'From ¥5,000 · Higashikawa', img: '/images/products/ceramics-mugs.jpg' },
        { title: 'Wood Craft Lamp', titleJa: '木工クラフトランプ', body: 'A layered, mushroom-shaped lamp turned from light Asahikawa timber. Warm light, quiet form - the kind of object that anchors a room.', bodyJa: '旭川の淡い木材から削り出した層状のきのこ型ランプ。温かな灯りと静かなフォルムが部屋を引き締めます。', price: '¥66,000 · Asahikawa', img: '/images/products/wood-lamp.jpg' },
      ].map((item, i) => (
        <div class="bg-brand-bg" data-fade style={`transition-delay:${(i % 4) * 60}ms`}>
          <div class="aspect-square overflow-hidden">
            <img src={item.img} alt={item.title} class="w-full h-full object-cover" />
          </div>
          <div class="p-6 md:p-8">
            <h4 class="font-display uppercase text-sm mb-2" data-en={item.title} data-ja={item.titleJa}>{item.title}</h4>
            <p class="text-brand-muted text-xs leading-relaxed" data-en={item.body} data-ja={item.bodyJa}>{item.body}</p>
            {item.price && <p class="text-brand-muted text-xs mt-3 font-medium">{item.price}</p>}
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Craftspeople -->
  <section class="px-8 md:px-16 pt-16 pb-10 md:pt-24 md:pb-16 border-t border-brand-border">
    <p class="text-[10px] tracking-[0.25em] uppercase text-brand-accent mb-8 flex items-center gap-4">
      <span data-en="The craftspeople" data-ja="職人たち">The craftspeople</span>
      <span class="block h-px w-12 bg-brand-accent/40"></span>
    </p>
    <h2 class="font-display uppercase leading-[1.1] mb-8" style="font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.25rem);"
      data-en="People who have been<br />here a long time"
      data-ja="この土地と<br />長く共に生きてきた人々"
    >
      People who have been<br />here a long time
    </h2>
    <p class="text-brand-muted text-sm leading-relaxed max-w-lg mb-14"
      data-en="Every object we curate has a story and an artist behind it. These are some of the people Studio Kaku works with - their knowledge of Hokkaido's materials and traditions is built into everything they produce."
      data-ja="私たちが選ぶすべての品には作り手がいます。Studio Kakuが協働する職人の一部をご紹介します——北海道の素材と伝統への深い知識が、彼らの作品のすべてに宿っています。"
    >
      Every object we curate has a story and an artist behind it. These are some of the people Studio Kaku works with - their knowledge of Hokkaido's materials and traditions is built into everything they produce.
    </p>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-px bg-brand-border">
      {[
        {
          img: '/images/craftspeople/taisetsugama.jpg',
          gen: 'Three generations · Hokkaido',
          genJa: '三代続く · 北海道',
          sub: 'Taisetsugama',
          subJa: '大雪窯',
          title: 'Where the landscape enters the glaze',
          titleJa: '風景が釉薬に宿る場所',
          body: 'A ceramics studio rooted entirely in its surroundings. Taisetsugama works across three series: hand-painted pieces depicting the hills and skies of Biei; a crystalline glaze technique passed down across three generations, where snow and ice formations emerge in the firing - never guaranteed, always unique; and a semi-porcelain line in warm ivory with vivid colour glazes that evoke freshly fallen snow in sunlight. Each piece is designed to feel as good in the hand as it looks on a shelf.',
          bodyJa: '環境と一体化した陶芸工房。大雪窯は三つのシリーズに取り組んでいます：美瑛の丘と空を描いた手描き作品、三代にわたり受け継がれた結晶釉の技法（焼成のたびに雪や氷の模様が生まれ、同じものは二つとない）、そして雪の白さに陽光が差し込む情景を思わせる鮮やかな色釉のセミ磁器ライン。どの作品も手に取ったときの感触と棚に飾ったときの佇まいを大切にしています。',
          detail: 'Painted ceramics · Crystalline glaze · Semi-porcelain · Bespoke vessels',
          detailJa: '手描き陶磁器 · 結晶釉 · セミ磁器 · オーダーメイド器',
          slug: 'taisetsugama',
        },
        {
          img: '/images/craftspeople/gallery-mingei.jpg',
          gen: 'Third generation · Est. 1906',
          genJa: '三代目 · 1906年創業',
          sub: 'Asahikawa & Sapporo',
          subJa: '旭川・札幌',
          title: 'A century of Hokkaido craft',
          titleJa: '北海道の工芸、一世紀の歩み',
          body: 'Founded in 1906 as a furniture shop in Asahikawa, this family-run gallery has been shaped by the Mingei folk craft movement for over a century. Now in its third generation, it has grown into a multi-location operation - Asahikawa, Sapporo, and the Shin-Furano Prince Hotel.',
          bodyJa: '1906年に旭川で家具店として創業。民芸運動の精神を一世紀以上受け継いできたこの一族経営のギャラリーは、現在三代目として旭川・札幌・新富良野プリンスホテルに展開しています。',
          detail: 'Tableware · Everyday objects · Clothing · Paintings · Prints · Sculpture',
          detailJa: '食器 · 日用品 · 衣類 · 絵画 · 版画 · 彫刻',
          slug: 'mingei-gallery',
        },
        {
          img: '/images/craftspeople/furniture-factory.jpg',
          gen: 'Tokyo-based · Factory in Higashikawa',
          genJa: '東京拠点 · 東川工場',
          sub: 'Higashikawa, Hokkaido',
          subJa: '北海道東川町',
          title: 'From log to finished piece, in-house',
          titleJa: '丸太から完成品まで、すべて自社で',
          body: 'A Japanese furniture and interiors brand with a factory in Higashikawa - a town where roughly 40% of residents are involved in woodworking. Around 30 craftsmen hand-finish each piece using locally sourced timber, with machinery kept to a minimum.',
          bodyJa: '東川町に工場を持つ日本の家具・インテリアブランド。住民の約40%が木工に携わるこの町で、約30人の職人が地元産木材を使い、機械を最小限に抑えて一点一点手仕上げしています。',
          detail: 'Solid timber furniture · Bespoke commissions · Interior joinery',
          detailJa: '無垢材家具 · カスタムオーダー · 内装建具',
          slug: 'higashikawa-furniture',
        },
      ].map((craft, i) => (
        <div class="bg-brand-bg flex flex-col" data-fade style={`transition-delay:${i * 80}ms`}>
          <div class="aspect-[4/3] overflow-hidden">
            <img src={craft.img} alt="" class="w-full h-full object-cover" />
          </div>
          <div class="p-10 md:p-12 flex flex-col flex-1">
            <p class="text-[10px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-brand-accent mb-1" data-en={craft.gen} data-ja={craft.genJa}>{craft.gen}</p>
            <p class="text-brand-muted text-xs mb-5 tracking-wide" data-en={craft.sub} data-ja={craft.subJa}>{craft.sub}</p>
            <h3 class="font-display uppercase leading-[1.2] mb-4" style="font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 1.8vw, 1.4rem);" data-en={craft.title} data-ja={craft.titleJa}>{craft.title}</h3>
            <p class="text-brand-muted text-sm leading-relaxed mb-5 flex-1" data-en={craft.body} data-ja={craft.bodyJa}>{craft.body}</p>
            <p class="text-brand-muted text-[11px] tracking-wide border-t border-brand-border pt-4 mb-5" data-en={craft.detail} data-ja={craft.detailJa}>{craft.detail}</p>
            <a href={`/stories/${craft.slug}`} class="flex items-center gap-2 text-brand-text text-[11px] tracking-wide group">
              <span data-en="Read the full story" data-ja="全文を読む">Read the full story</span>
              <span class="group-hover:translate-x-1 transition-transform">→</span>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Service tiers -->
  <section class="px-8 md:px-16 pt-16 pb-10 md:pt-24 md:pb-16 border-t border-brand-border bg-brand-border/20">
    <p class="text-[10px] tracking-[0.25em] uppercase text-brand-accent mb-8 flex items-center gap-4">
      <span data-en="How we work" data-ja="サービスについて">How we work</span>
      <span class="block h-px w-12 bg-brand-accent/40"></span>
    </p>
    <h2 class="font-display uppercase leading-[1.1] mb-8" style="font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.25rem);"
      data-en="Choose the level<br />that suits you."
      data-ja="あなたに合った<br />プランをお選びください。"
    >
      Choose the level<br />that suits you.
    </h2>
    <p class="text-brand-muted text-sm leading-relaxed max-w-lg mb-14"
      data-en="Each plan covers consultation, curation, and installation - everything managed by us. If you already have pieces you love - artwork or furniture you want to ship in from elsewhere - we can arrange installation for those too. A well-curated space commands attention. The plan you choose shapes how far we take it."
      data-ja="すべてのプランにはコンサルテーション、キュレーション、設置が含まれ、一括管理します。すでにお持ちの作品や、他から取り寄せたい家具がある場合も、その設置を手配することができます。丁寧にキュレーションされた空間は人の心を動かします。プランの選択が、どこまで追求するかを決めます。"
    >
      Each plan covers consultation, curation, and installation - everything managed by us. If you already have pieces you love - artwork or furniture you want to ship in from elsewhere - we can arrange installation for those too. A well-curated space commands attention. The plan you choose shapes how far we take it.
    </p>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-px bg-brand-border">
      <!-- Entry Plan -->
      <div class="bg-brand-bg p-10 md:p-12" data-fade style="transition-delay:0ms">
        <h3 class="font-display uppercase leading-[1.15] mb-2" style="font-size: clamp(1rem, 1.8vw, 1.35rem);"
          data-en="Entry<br />Plan"
          data-ja="エントリー<br />プラン"
        >Entry<br />Plan</h3>
        <p class="text-brand-accent text-[11px] tracking-wide mb-6"
          data-en="A curated selection, yours to explore"
          data-ja="厳選されたセレクション、自由にお選びください"
        >A curated selection, yours to explore</p>
        <p class="font-display leading-none text-brand-text mb-1" style="font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 2.5vw, 2rem);">¥400,000</p>
        <p class="text-brand-muted text-xs mb-6" data-en="studio fee · pieces priced separately" data-ja="スタジオ料金 · 作品代別途">studio fee · pieces priced separately</p>
        <p class="text-brand-muted text-sm leading-relaxed mb-8"
          data-en="We put together a selection of art, objects, and framed works from our studio practice - chosen with your villa in mind. Browse, tell us what speaks to you, and we handle everything from there."
          data-ja="スタジオのプラクティスから、ヴィラを念頭に選んだアート、オブジェ、額装作品のセレクションをご提案します。気に入ったものをお伝えいただければ、あとはすべてお任せください。"
        >
          We put together a selection of art, objects, and framed works from our studio practice - chosen with your villa in mind. Browse, tell us what speaks to you, and we handle everything from there.
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-0 border-t border-brand-border pt-5">
          {[
            ['A private studio selection, ready to browse', 'プライベートなスタジオセレクション、自由にご覧いただけます'],
